init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is no longer the most powerful nation on earth.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is now a third world country, and the only nation that has not joined a collective.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world is a much safer place.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The other countries respond by saying that they did not need to isolate themselves because they were not the ones who started the war.
